==Hinduism in Latvia==
Hinduism is a minority religion in [[Latvia]]. As of 2011, there were 190 Hindus in Latvia. As of 2011, the Justice Ministry had registered 11 [[International Society for Krishna Consciousness|Hare Krishna]] and two other Hindu congregations in Latvia.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20121126013327/http://www.tm.gov.lv/lv/labumi/TM.docx</ref>

Brahma Kumaris have three centres in Latvia: in [[Riga]], [[Daugavpils]], and [[Rēzekne]].<ref>http://www.bkwsu.org//whereweare/center</ref>
[[Nath]] traditions also exist in Latvia. [[Gorakhnath]] mandir was established in 2011. Masters of Nath tradition go there to hold public [[satsang]]s and educational programmes. The Hindu festivals ([[Shivaratri]], [[Navaratri]], etc) are celebrated in the mandir as well.<ref>http://heyevent.com/venue/olknkjetqzimca</ref>

